Houses are far apart. Most houses are two stories. Some have metal roofs. Some have gray roofs. Houses are far from the road. This is so people can grow food on their land.

The town has one stoplight. It is at a four way. There are stores near the stoplight. 

There are three fast food places. One sells Chinese food. One sells Mexican food. One sells hamburgers. There is also a small drug store. They sell Cherry Coca-Cola. There is a small grocery store. Many people go to a bigger store in a nearby town. The most popular store is Dollar General. It sells many things. 

There is a small furniture store. It has a pet groomer next to it. There is a doctor and a vet. They help people and animals. There is one small school. Children go to school in another town for middle and high school. 

There are no parks in the town. But they are making a small park. There are not many things to do in the town. There are no movies, bowling, or playgrounds.

The town is small. You may miss it!

I hear talk about my area on a radio show. The show talk about people who go missing. It is strange. The apartments here cost a lot of money. I never hear about this story. My friends do not know about it. Things are hard for many people. Some of my friends feel sad. Things are expensive. We learn to use money well. We like old things. We like to go to stores that sell used goods. 

There are many stores near my home. You can walk to three stores that sell used things. You can also go to a library and a store with old books. The town is busy. There are many cars and people. But the stores are quiet. It is good to go to the stores. You can spend time there.

The town is growing. More people come to live here. It is like New York City. People are busy. They work hard. They do not talk much to each other. You can be alone here. People do not ask you for help. It is different from the South. In the South, people care about each other. They ask questions. You can be alone here. People will not bother you.

I live with my neighbors. We are like friends. We help each other. We have parties and we help each other when someone is sad. I am happy to live here. I like my neighbors. We are good to each other.

I live in a suburb. It is like many other suburbs. My area has a home owner group. 

The homes look alike. They are all single family homes. The yards are small. They have grass, rocks, and short driveways. Most homes have a two car garage. The roads are new and good. There are no holes. Some homes are one story. Some homes are two stories. 

We do not have mailboxes at each home. There is one big place for mailboxes at the end of the street. People use a key to open their mailbox. There are also big boxes for packages.

My home is near a city. So my area is like a mix of city and country. We have space. There are pools and trails for walking.

Many people in my area are old. It is a safe place. People look out for each other. There are also some middle-aged and young people.

The city is big. But it feels small. We have stores. We have one mall. It is not very big. I drive about fifteen minutes to get to many stores. We have good stores and cheap stores.

My area is good. It is safe and clean. We have good things like pools and trails. We are not close to many stores. But it is easy to drive to stores.

I live in a small town. It is near a big city. My home is on the east side. This side is not rich. Houses are old. Many people do not have much money. My neighbors are kind. They say hello. Crime is not very high here, but there are some bad things. A few years ago, a man was hurt near my home. My neighbor lost his son in a bad fight. We have not had problems, but things go miss sometimes from our porch. Our town has a big problem with drugs. Many people use drugs. Some people die. There are places to help people who use drugs. My son goes to school here. The teachers are good. He likes school. His school helps families. The school gives free food to all children. No one feels bad if they do not have much money. The town is trying to make things better. They are fixing roads and parks. Most of this work is in the center of town. My side is old and needs work. I like my town. The people are nice. The school is good. There are stores to buy things. Our house is small, but it is good enough. We have lived here for a long time. We like it here.

My area has much culture. It is on a hill with old buildings. I live in a tall building. It is near an old theater. I walk to a small bar with games. Many people go there on warm nights. 

There is a big park near my home. It has walls and steps. In winter, some people sleep in tents near the park. They stay close to keep warm. They can walk to a center for help. 

I like my area. The people are kind. My area was bad in the past. There was much bad crime. The people remember. They work hard to keep it safe. Some say it is bad at night. I think this is old thinking.

Many people here are not like me. They are not white. I feel safe here. People are nice to me.  They help me when I need it.

My area is home. I feel good here.

I live in a small town in Michigan. It is in rural area. There are farms and small towns near me. There are no big stores. There is no Walmart, Target, or Applebee's. You must drive to go to these places. 

I live in a very pretty place. It is near two lakes: Lake Michigan and Lake Charlevoix. You can go to the beach near my home.

My town is small. The houses are not close together. They are old houses. Some houses are new. Many houses have basements. Most houses have aluminum siding. The houses are many colors. Most houses have yards. 

The people in my town work hard. They have families. You see children playing outside. You see people walking dogs and biking. People know each other. 

The yards are clean. The grass is cut. The plants are trimmed. My town is not very fancy. It is a good place to raise a family. It is safe and quiet.

There is a police station, a jail, and a health center near my home. We have a recycling center. There are baseball and softball fields. You can hear the games. There is a small airport. You can hear planes taking off and landing.

You can walk to get ice cream. You can walk to downtown. My children can bike to the park. It is a good place to live.
